    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>One of the three major divisions of living organisms; includes plants, animals, and all living things other than Archaea and Eubacteria. Although members in this group differ greatly, all members of the group have eukaryotic cells with a nucleus that contain genetic material within chromosomes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
